oMLX  (https://github.com/jundot/omlx)  — Apache-2.0
  mlx-mtp's quantizer (mlx_mtp/oq_quantize.py) drives oMLX's streaming `oQ`
  quantizer, and its engine relies on oMLX's mlx-vlm MTP runtime patch
  (omlx.patches.mlx_vlm_mtp) to attach the embedded MTP head. Portions of
  the approach and interfaces are derived from oMLX.

MTPLX  (https://github.com/youssofal/MTPLX)  — see upstream license
  The native multi-token-prediction speculative-decoding method (draft via the
  model's own MTP head, verify, probability-ratio accept + residual) that
  mlx-mtp re-implements for vision-language models is from MTPLX.

mlx, mlx-lm, mlx-vlm  (https://github.com/ml-explore , https://github.com/Blaizzy/mlx-vlm)
  The inference engine. mlx-mtp calls mlx-vlm internals
  (rollback_speculative_cache, capture_layer_ids, speculative._speculative_walk,
  speculative.mtp/dflash helpers).

DFlash  (z-lab/Qwen3.6-27B-DFlash)
  External block-diffusion drafter used by the DFlash and hybrid paths.

mlx-optiq  (https://mlx-optiq.com)
  Reference for mixed-precision MLX quantization ("optiq").
